.TH "ufshcd_query_attr" 9 "ufshcd_query_attr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ufshcd_query_attr \- API function for sending attribute requests
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ufshcd_query_attr
.BI "(struct ufs_hba *hba "  ","
.BI "enum query_opcode opcode "  ","
.BI "enum attr_idn idn "  ","
.BI "u8 index "  ","
.BI "u8 selector "  ","
.BI "u32 *attr_val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hba" 12
per-adapter instance
.IP "opcode" 12
attribute opcode
.IP "idn" 12
attribute idn to access
.IP "index" 12
index field
.IP "selector" 12
selector field
.IP "attr_val" 12
the attribute value after the query request completes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 for success, non-zero in case of failure
